premise_source_doc_sentence: William West Anderson  (  born September 19 , 1928  )  , better known as Adam West , is an American actor whose career spans six decades .
His acting career began in films in 1959 .
He played opposite Chuck Connors in Geronimo  (  1962  )  and The Three Stooges in The Outlaws Is Coming  (  1965  )  .

He has also appeared in the science-fiction film Robinson Crusoe on Mars  (  1964  )  , opposite Paul Mantee , and achieved continuing success for the title role in the 1960s ABC series Batman and its theatrical feature film .

He has done voice work on The Fairly OddParents , The Simpsons and Family Guy  (  he voices fictional versions of himself in all of those animated series  )  and also Batman : Return of the Caped Crusaders .
Adam West  (  born 1928  )  is an American actor best known for playing Batman on a popular 1960s television series .
